Tusken Raiders, less formally referred to as Sand People or simply as Tuskens, are a culture of nomadic, primitive sentients indigenous to Tatooine, where they are quite hostile to local settlers. The term Sand People was given to them due to their existence in the desert, and has been in use from at least 4,000 BBY; but the more formal name of Tusken Raiders was acquired much later, due to a period of concerted attacks on the settlement at Fort Tusken in 98-95 BBY. This later became the definitive name for the species.

Specialists studying the past of the Tusken Raiders also use the term Ghorfa to denote an earlier sedentary phase of their culture, and lastly Kumumgah, for the earliest stratum of sentient civilization on the planet, believed by some to represent a common ancestry shared by the Ghorfa and the Jawas.

This rifle consists of little more than a single long barrel that was an amalgamation of a number of pipes and long metal parts. Its only distinct feature, in fact, was a carrying handle that protruded from the side of the weapon.

Unlike most commonly found rifles, these do not emit laser blasts. Mustafarian skin alone is enough to disperse the heat of most blaster bolts, and the addition of armor renders lasers totally useless against them. Their rifles instead discharge kinetic energy condensed into bolts.

A blaster is a ranged weapon that fires bursts of particle beam energy called blaster bolts from a replaceable power cell. The most commonly used weapon in the Galaxy, blasters' intense beams consisting of compacted high-energy particles and intense light can kill or paralyze their target, depending on their setting.

The gaderffii, or gaffi stick, is the traditional melee weapon of the Tusken Raiders of Tatooine. Crafted out of whatever salvage is at hand, they are very effective in close combat. Nearly every Tusken is proficient in the use of these weapons and more Tuskens chose the gaffi over the Tusken Cycler.
